Copa México 1940-41 (Cup Tournament)

NB: Moctezuma and Selección Jalisco did not enter

[Mar 30]
América 2 Marte 1
  [Luis García Cortina (2); Luis de la Fuente]

[Apr 6]
Necaxa 3 Atlante 2
  [Cervantes (2), Tomás Lozano; Martín Vantolrá, José Zamudio]

[Apr 13]
Asturias unk España
  [Asturias won]

[Apr 17]
América 1 Asturias 9

[Apr 20]
Atlante 2 Marte 2 [aet]

[Apr 24]
*América 2 España 6
*América eliminated

Replay
[Apr 27]
*Marte 5 Atlante 2
  [Headley (3), José Luis Borbolla, Luis de la Fuente; Medina, Pradere]
*Atlante eliminated
+Necaxa 0 Asturias 1
  [Enrique Larriñaga]
+Asturias bye to final

[May 4]
*España 4 Marte 2
  [Martín Cuburu (3), José Iraragorri; Luis de la Fuente (2)]
*Marte eliminated

[May 11]
*Necaxa 2 España 4
  [¿?; Rodolfo Muñoz, Martín Cuburu, Cabalceta, Emilio Alonso]
*Necaxa eliminated

Final
[May 18]
Parque Asturias, Mexico City
*Asturias 2 España 2 [aet]
  [Eguirao, Ordóñez; Quezada, Rodolfo Muñoz]
*España refused to play the Replay match, Asturias was declared champion


